read

public static SimulationNonCompressedUWI read(java.lang.String filename,
                                              java.lang.String filter,
                                              java.lang.String[] exactNames)
                                       throws java.io.IOException
constructs a noncompressed UWI database (.NCA, .NCD, .NCF, .NCH) from the provided file.

The header filename is derived from filename by changing its extension to .HDR

Parameters:
filename - filename from which to read the body.
filter - java regular expression. Signals whose name match the expression are loaded. Use ".*" to load all, use "" to load only the requested exactNames
exactNames - String[] of names. Signals whose name exactly match one of the entries are loaded. Pass new String[0] to match none
Returns:
the requested simulation data
Throws:
java.io.IOException

getSourceDescription

public java.lang.String getSourceDescription()
Description copied from interface: LoadableSignalDatabase
Return a String that provides information about the file by which this database is backed up. Load signals will retrieve data from this source.

For most readers, this call should simply return the filename of the file that has been read.

For readers with a separate header and body, it should provide both, separated with a "; "

Code should not depend on the exact form of this field
